QUEEN (gyne). Ergatoid (e.g. CASENT0248384). TL 6.8, HL 1.28, HW 0.93-0.97, CI 73-76, SL 1.35-1.38, SI 142-145, WL 1.72-1.74, MfL 1.70-1.72, MfL/HW 1.77-1.83, MfL/MfH 7.17-7.53. EL 0.24-0.25 (EL/HW 
0.26
) (2 measured). Propodeal spine length ca 0.46, but the spines stouter than in the worker. Postpetiole length 0.60, width 0.58-0.60, height 0.60-0.63. Maximum width of first gastral tergite 1.50-1.60 (as opposed to <1.30 in worker). Most dimensions are within the worker ranges, but the scape is relatively shorter, and the metafemur is both absolutely and relatively shorter. In general the ergatoid matches the worker description, but the pronotal sculpture is more sharply reticulate-rugose, and the humeral angles are more pronounced. Pilosity as worker but head without the posterior transverse row (this may have been abraded away in the single specimen available). Ocelli absent or at most with a pit-like vestige of the median ocellus among the cephalic sculpture.
